The paper deals with the problem of single image rain streaks removal using deep convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for this task, which involves enhancing feature expression and spatial correlation learning. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of dense blocks to capture long-distance dependencies and structural information, which suggests that it may also fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on both synthetic and real datasets, indicating that it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
